commands.name: az network manager routing-config create
commands.summary: Create a network manager routing configuration.
examples: az network manager routing-config create --name TestNetworkManagerConfig --manager-name TestNetworkManager --resource-group "rg1"

commands.name: az network manager routing-config delete
commands.summary: Delete a network manager routing configuration.
commands.syntax:
az network manager routing-config delete [--config-name]
                                         [--ids]
                                         [--manager-name]
                                         [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                         [--resource-group]
                                         [--subscription]
                                         [--yes]
examples: az network manager routing-config delete --name TestNetworkManagerConfig --manager-name TestNetworkManager --resource-group "rg1" -y

commands.name: az network manager routing-config list
commands.summary: List all the network manager routing configurations in a network manager, in a paginated format.
examples: az network manager routing-config list --manager-name TestNetworkManager --resource-group "rg1"

commands.name: az network manager routing-config show
commands.summary: Get a network manager routing configuration.
examples: az network manager routing-config show --name TestNetworkManagerConfig --manager-name TestNetworkManager --resource-group "rg1"

commands.name: az network manager routing-config update
commands.summary: Update a network manager routing configuration.
commands.syntax:
az network manager routing-config update [--add]
                                         [--config-name]
                                         [--description]
                                         [--force-string {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                         [--ids]
                                         [--manager-name]
                                         [--remove]
                                         [--resource-group]
                                         [--set]
                                         [--subscription]
examples: az network manager routing-config update --name TestNetworkManagerConfig --manager-name TestNetworkManager --resource-group "rg1" --description "test"

commands.name: az network manager routing-config wait
commands.summary: Place the CLI in a waiting state until a condition is met.
